depends quadratically on x:

x + c(x2- l)x + x = 0

where c is a positive constant. It is convenient to use Lienard's transformation
(Lienard, 1928; Minorsky, 1947):

y = X/c + x3/3 - x
and obtain the following pair of differential equations:
