Like the HH equations, the BVP equations can be more easily understood by
considering separately the behavior of two subsystems. y is a more slowly changing
variable than x (except near the y nullcdlne). If y is kept constant at any value
= 0), instead of being allowed to vary according to equation (2), the corre-

