the end of the pulse, when z returns discontinuously to zero, the phase plane of
Fig. 1 is restored. If the phase point at that instant is to the left of the separatrix in
the z = 0 phase plane, excitation occurs. This case differs from that of an instantane-
ous current pulse (T -O 0) only in that, at the end of the pulse, y has increased
somewhat, and a somewhat greater value of ax is needed to carry the phase point to
the separatrix.

A constant anodal current (positive z) moves the x nullcline downward (Fig. 4).

