to produce a limit cycle is applied to the resting BVP model, the phase point passes
from P and approaches the limit cycle C, and an infinite train of impulses results
(see Fig. 2, middle).

As a final example, the more complicated phenomenon of "break reexcitation"
in heart muscle (Cranefield and Hoffman, 1958; Hoffman and Cranefield, 1960)
also seems to have a reasonable explanation in terms of BVP physiological state
diagrams. An anodal shock of proper strength applied locally during the plateau of

